OL,3,C'Prisoner in her own home' risk for
OL,4,Cdisabled woman as funding falls short
OL,6,F"There will come a point that
OL,7,FCharlotte will become a prisoner in
OL,8,Fher own home," Robert Parker said.
OL,9,F"She could end up stuck in her
OL,10,Fbedroom, not able to spend time with
OL,11,Fher family or make memories with her
OL,12,Fchildren."
OL,14,FUntil recently, West Berkshire Council
OL,15,Falso offered up to #20,000 in
OL,16,Fdiscretionary top-up funding. But the
OL,17,Ffamily were informed this has now been
OL,18,Fwithdrawn due to budget pressures and
OL,19,Fincreasing numbers of applicants.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
