OL,3,C'Prisoner in her own home' risk for
OL,4,Cdisabled woman as funding falls short
OL,6,FTheir struggle echoes findings from a
OL,7,Fnew report by the Motor Neurone
OL,8,FDisease Association, which warns of
OL,9,Flong delays and insufficient funding
OL,10,Ffor crucial home adaptations
OL,11,Fnationwide.
OL,13,FRichard Evans said: "Half of people
OL,14,Fwith MND die within two years of
OL,15,Fdiagnosis. The idea that they have to
OL,16,Fwait an average of a year for
OL,17,Fadaptations is a scandal. This isn't
OL,18,Facceptable in 21st century Britain."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
